FTP Server Setup Script

This script installs and configures the vsftpd FTP server on an Ubuntu system.

How to Run the Script
Clone the Repository or Download the Script: Ensure you have the script file named setup-ftp.sh.

Make the Script Executable: Run the following command to give execute permissions to the script:

sh
Copy code
chmod +x setup-ftp.sh
Run the Script: Execute the script with sudo privileges:

sh
Copy code
sudo ./setup-ftp.sh
